1. `∀ x, B x` is a bounded linear map.
2. `∀ x, ∀ y, ∀ c, (B x) (c • y) = c • (B x) y` (map_smul_right)
3. `∀ x, ∀ y, ∀ c, (B (c • x)) y = c • (B x) y` (map_smul_left)
4. `∀ x, ∀ y, ∀ c, (B x) (y + c • y₁) = (B x) y + c • (B x) y₁` (map_add_right)
